					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You'd have to get the CPU to execute your code at a time that doesn't interfere with the game's execution.<br /><br />Essentially what you're trying to build is the Pro Action Replay accessory. It intercepts calls to the NMI vector, which gets called 60 times per second (once at the start of each vertical blanking period). When NMI occurs, the accessory somehow intercepts the vector and calls code that interacts with the RAM.</div>

