			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Your hardware will need to detect reads from $00FFEA, $00FFFA, and $00FFFC (native NMI, 6502 NMI, and reset), and have such reads toggle a switch between enabling the cartridge and enabling your piggyback board. When NMI occurs, the CPU will push flags and the return address and then read $00FFEA-$00FFEB. This will trigger a switch to a program on your piggyback board, which pushes all registers to the stack, does what it wants with the RAM at $7E0000-$7FFFFF, pops registers, and chains to the game's own NMI handler using JMP ($FFEA). This causes a second read of $00FFEA, which switches the cart back in.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
